urname>Logothetis</surname><given-names>DE</given-names></name></person-group><year>2005</year><article-title>PI(4,5)P2 regulates the activation and desensitization of TRPM8 channels through the TRP domain.</article-title><source>Nat Neurosci</source><volume>8</volume><fpage>626</fpage><lpage>634</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">15852009</pub-id></citation></ref><ref id="pone.0005741-Jordt1"><label>21</label><citation citation-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Jordt</surname><given-names>SE</given-names></name><name><surname>Julius</surname><given-names>D</given-names></name></person-group><year>2002</year><article-title>Molecular basis for species-specific sensitivity to &#x0201c;hot&#x0201d; chili peppers.</article-title><source>Cell</source><volume>108</volume><fpage>421</fpage><lpage>430</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">11853675</pub-id></citation></ref><ref id="pone.0005741-Nathans1"><label>22</label><citation citation-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Nathans</surname><given-names>J</given-names></name></person-group><year>1999</year><article-title>The evolution and physiology of human color vision: insights from molecular genetic studies of visual pigments.</article-title><source>Neuron</source><volume>24</volume><fpage>299</fpage><lpage>312</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">10571225</pub-id></citation></ref><ref id="pone.0005741-Niimura1"><label>23</label><citation citation-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Niimura</surname><given-names>Y</given-names></name><name><surname>Nei</surname><given-names>M</given-names></name></person-group><year>2006</year><article-title>Evolutionary dynamics of olfactory and other chemosensory receptor genes in vertebrates.</article-title><source>J Hum Genet</source><volume>51</volume><fpage>505</fpage><lpage>517</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">16607462</pub-id></citation></ref><ref id="pone.0005741-Banker1"><label>